bcm2835
------------------------------------------
This is a C library for Raspberry Pi (RPi). It provides access to GPIO and
other IO functions on the Broadcom BCM 2835 chip, allowing access to the GPIO
pins on the 26 pin IDE plug on the RPi board so you can control and interface
with various external devices.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.2.1-1
  libbcm2835-devel-1.45-1bl1
  libbcm2835_0-1.45-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-2
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.airspayce.com/mikem/bcm2835/

Canonical download:
  http://www.airspayce.com/mikem/bcm2835/bcm2835-1.45.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bcm2835-1.45-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bcm2835-1.45-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bcm2835-1.45-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bcm2835-1.45-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbcm2835_0-1.45-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbcm2835-devel-1.45-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bcm2835)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bcm2835.README
  /usr/share/doc/bcm2835/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/bcm2835/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/bcm2835/README

(libbcm2835_0)
  /usr/bin/cygbcm2835-0.dll

(libbcm2835-devel)
  /usr/include/bcm2835.h
  /usr/lib/libbcm2835.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/bcm2835.pc

